Indianapolis; and\nMiss Kate Curry, Indianapoli.\npresidents;\nkomo, treasurer.\nVictor Garrigus,\nvice\nKo\nMRS. COOLIDGE TO GAME\nMrs. Coolidge, accompanied by a\nparty of friends, left here at noon\nby motor to attend the Princeton\nNavy football game at Baltimore.\nThe wife of the commander in chief/\nj of the navy wore Navy colors.\nBUS HEARINGS SOON\nPublic hearings will be held Mon\nday, Nov. 12, at the District build\ning i\nsion.\nby the public utilities commis\nApplications by the Washing\nton Electric and Railway Co., to ex\ntend its motor bus line from 19th-st\nand Virginia-av nw to the Lincoln\nMemorial will be considered.\nThe bus line now operates from\n17th and H streets to 19th and Vir\nit issues free transfers to\nginia-av.\nthe company\u2019s street cars.\nPREPARE FOR HALLOWE\u2019EN\nPlay space for children Hallowe\u2019en\nnight was provided by the commis\nVermont-av be' ween\nsioner today.\nThomas-cir and N-sts nw will be\nclosed to vehicle traffic from 6:30\np. m. to 11 p. m.\nRhode I-land-av\nbetween 20 and 22d-st ne will be\nclosed from 8:80 p. m. until 11:30\np. m.\nNew York Curb;\nINDUSTRIALS\u2014\nHigh Low Close 1\nAmer G&E....\n40\nBridgeport Mach. 101\nDurant Motors..\n29\n40\n10%\n26\nGillette S R.... 265% 265\nGoodyear Tire...\nHudson Co. pfd.\nInercon Rub....\n9%\n19\n3\n9%\n18\n3\n40\n10%\n28%\n265\n9%\n18%\n3\nN Y Tel pfd.... 1097s 109% 109%\nRadio\nSwift Inter\n17\nB\n27,\n3\n2%\n11 S Lt Ht, pfd 80\nUnited P Shar..\nUnited II C A..\nYellow Tax, N Y 126\n6%\n5%\n17%\n80\n6%\n5%\n126\n8\n17%\n80\n6%\n5%\n126\nINDEPENDENT OIL\nCities Ser. 129%- 129\nDerby Oil com..\nGulf Oil of Pa..\nMex Oil\nMutual Oil, vtc..\nOmar Oil.\nRoyal Can. Oil..\nSalt Creek Prod.\n6\n52\n73\n9%\n65\n3%\n18%\n534\n52\n70\n9%.\n60\n3%\n12912\n5%\n52\n9\n8\nSapulpa Ref.... 100\nSeab\u2019d Oil Gas 95\nSouth States Oil\n15%\nIS1\n80\n95\n\n15%\n65\n3%\n18%\n81\n95\n15%\nSTANDARD OIL\u2014\nAnglo Amer Oil.\nBack Pipe Line.\nGalena Sig Oil..\nImperial Oil, Can\n